text: Great place to get a bite near gate d17. Fast and not  cold. Cal pizza kitchen took 30 min before they attempted to take our order. This was fast, friendly and fresh. Maybe the best kept secret in terminal 1 d gates.

My first puck experience other than pizza. What s lame disappointment. 

I'm writing this half hour after arriving. I cannot get attention of the waitress to get a drink. 

The cook does not know what's in the food ( diet issue). 

Just a mess. Pretty much a low end chain so not sure why he's so popular.

I am rarely one to complain, especially about airport food, but this Italian Bistro sandwich is possibly one of the worst sandwiches I've ever had. If the soggy, thickly cut white bread masked by the name "sough dough" doesn't turn you off, the herbed mayo slapped onto the outside of it definitely will - and earn you a few crumpled napkins. If you dare to continue, ignore the mediocre cold cuts inside and just eat the side of chips. Not worth it.
